      "coverage_goals": {},
      "demo_behavior": "Module: TopModule I would like you to implement a module named TopModule with the following interface. All input and output ports are one bit unless otherwise specified. - input  clk - input  L - input  q_in - input  r_in - output Q Consider this Verilog module \"full_module\": module full_module ( input [2:0] r, input L, input clk, output reg [2:0] q); always @(posedge clk) begin if (L) begin q <= r; end else begin q <= {q[1] ^ q[2], q[0], q[2]}; end end endmodule Note that q[2:0] is three bits wide, representing three flip-flops that can be loaded from r when L is asserted. You want to factor full_module into a hierarchical design, flipflop and 2:1 multiplexer are in a submodule \"TopModule\", and that submodule will be instantiated three times in full_module code. Create the submodule called \"TopModule\". You do not have to provide the revised full_module.\nKey rules: Implement behavior exactly as described in the prompt.\nReset: Only as explicitly described in the prompt.\nCorner cases: No additional corner cases beyond prompt requirements.\nPerformance: Use prompt-defined timing/latency behavior.",
